{
  "texts": [
    "A potential solution lies in scanning these archives into image format and subsequently converting them into a machine-readable format-a process known as AHR.",
    "While AHR is commonly associated with historical document recognition, its applications extend to various beneficial uses, as summarized in Fig. 1.",
    "The complex nature of the Arabic script introduces intricacies into AHR, resulting in limited satisfactory tools compared to non-cursive languages and printed text.",
    "The influence of the Arabic script extends to languages like Farsi, Urdu, and Jawi [2], all based on the Arabic script and incorporating additional characters and diacritics.",
    "Despite adaptations, these scripts share fundamental similarities with the Arabic script, making the characteristics and challenges discussed in this section pertinent not only to Arabic but also to numerous languages sharing similar features."
  ]
}